President Obama has appointed Cindy S. Moelis as the Director for the Presidential Commission on White House Fellows. The program, established in 1964 by President Lyndon B. Johnson, aims to encourage active citizenship and service to the nation. Moelis, who previously served as the Executive Director of the Pritzker Traubert Family Foundation, has a background in education reform and fighting social justice challenges. She holds a degree from the Wharton School of Business at the University of Pennsylvania and a J.D. from Stanford Law School.